<h1>Spotify Chatbot</h1>
This is a simple Telegram chatbot that uses the Spotify API and OpenAI's GPT-3 model to provide information about tracks, artists, and albums on Spotify.

Features
Provides information about tracks, artists, and albums on Spotify
Uses OpenAI's GPT-3 model to generate responses
Uses the Spotify API to search for track, artist, and album information
Setup
Clone the repository:
```
git clone https://github.com/ogabek0302/spotify-chatbot.git
```
Install the dependencies:

```
pip install -r requirements.txt
```
Create a Telegram bot and get its API token from BotFather

Create a Spotify developer account and create a new app to get the client ID and client secret

Create an OpenAI developer account and get the API key

Create a file named .env in the root directory of the project and add the following lines:

TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=<YOUR_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN>
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=<YOUR_SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID>
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=<YOUR_SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET>
OPENAI_API_KEY=<YOUR_OPENAI_API_KEY>

<h1>Run the bot:</h1>
```
python main.py
```
Usage
To use the bot, simply start a chat with it on Telegram and type in the name of the track, artist, or album you're interested in. The bot will respond with information about the search query.

Here are some example commands:

/start or /help - Displays a welcome message and instructions on how to use the bot
/track <track_name> - Searches for information about a specific track
/artist <artist_name> - Searches for information about a specific artist
/album <album_name> - Searches for information about a specific album